Opposition chief and ODM party leader Raila Odinga was among thousands of Kenyans who turned up to view the body of the late retired president Daniel Arap Moi at parliament buildings. Odinga described the former president as a cheerful man since he knew him in 1958. Other leaders who paid their last respects to mzee Moi include chief justice David Moraga, wiper party leader Kalonzo Musyoka as well as legislators who had attended a special sitting.